se.cbb.jprime.topology

Interface AcyclicDigraph

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Graph
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RootedBifurcatingTree, RootedBifurcatingTreeParameter, RootedTree, RootedTreeParameter
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RBTree, RTree

    public interface AcyclicDigraph
extends Graph
    Interface for implementations of acyclic digraphs (commonly referred to as 'DAGs'). The interface allows multiple disjoint components, although implementations/sub-interfaces may of course specialise to contain only one. See the super-interface for more details.
    Author:

      • hasArc

        boolean hasArc(int x,
             int y)
        Returns true if there is an arc (x,y). By definition, hasArc(x,x) will always return false due to graph acyclicity.
        Parameters:
        x - the tentative tail vertex.
        y - the tentative head vertex.
        Returns:
        true if there is an arc (x,y).

      • hasPath

        boolean hasPath(int x,
              int y)
        Returns true if there is a path from x to y, i.e. y is a proper successor of x. By definition, hasPath(x,x) will always return false due to graph acyclicity.
        Parameters:
        x - the tentative predecessor.
        y - the tentative proper successor.
        Returns:
        true if there is a path from x to y.

      • getSuccessorSinks

        java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> getSuccessorSinks(int x)
        Returns all "descendants" with out-degree 0 of a vertex x, excluding x itself. If no descendant sinks exist, an empty list is returned. The list is not guaranteed to be sorted or in any particular order. A null-graph returns null.
        Returns:
        the sink successor vertices.

      • getTopologicalOrdering

        Returns:
